text:
Been here a few times and find the taste is very good.
Fish soup - fish slices are very fresh but soup is too salty. The chili is good. Ideal if can add other vege too.
Zichar - minced pork tofu, honey pork, prawn paste chicken all delicious.
First time at this new coffeeshop (FoodHub). Had this salted egg diced chicken rice with egg from Mata Thai. Not bad. $7 pretty reasonable like the usual Tze char stall. üòÄüëçüèº

Shop was originally Mata Thai but just changed to Nanyang Fish Soup few weeks back.
Had a good first experience there with great variety and decent food. Wish them all the best.
Shop and environment is great too, very airy and lots of space.

Recently moved to woodland glen. A place to avoid at all cost. They'd rip you off your money. There are better stall to spend and eat tasty dishes from. They charge exorbitant prices for dishes. Daylight robbery. Preferred the old stall before this stall came about. Also, please teach your  china workers in the stall counter  basic Engrish.
